|Siu juk
|}

[[Image:HongKongstreetloumei.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Street [[lou mei]]]]

===Lou mei===
{{main|Lou mei}}
[[Lou mei]] is the name given to dishes made from the [[offal|internal organs]], [[entrail]]s and left-over parts of animals. It is grouped under Siu laap (燒臘) as part of Cantonese cuisine. It is widely available in Southern Chinese regions.

