[[Image:Littlebowlrice.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Little pan rice]]

===Little pan rice===
Little pan rice ([[wikt:煲|煲]][[wikt:仔|仔]][[wikt:飯|飯]], bou1 zai2 faan6) are dishes that are cooked and served in a flat-bottomed pan (as opposed to a round-bottomed [[wok]]). Usually it is a [[Cookware and bakeware|saucepan]] or [[braising]] [[Clay pot cooking|pan]]. Such dishes are cooked by covering and steaming, making the rice and ingredients very hot and soft. Usually the ingredients are layered on top of the rice with little to no mixing in between. Quite a number of ingredients are used with many standard combinations.

{| class=&quot;wikitable&quot;
|-
