*Boudin balls - Boudin sausage filling that is rolled into a ball, battered and deep fried, instead of being stuffed into pork casings.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=uha0mHZ-N8oC&amp;lpg=PA141&amp;ots=D_tqH6GuQC&amp;dq=%22boudin%20ball%22&amp;pg=PA141#v=onepage&amp;q=%22boudin%20ball%22&amp;f=false|title=500 Things to Eat Before It's Too Late: And the Very Best Places to Eat Them|author=Michael Stern|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt, 2009|isbn=0547059078, 9780547059075|accessdate=2009-11-24}}&lt;/ref&gt;
*Poutine - A traditional Sunday supper deriving from the French &quot;Beouf Bourgignon&quot; but served with a thick gravy from which it derives its name Poutine, meaning &quot;pudding&quot;. Served over white rice, the stewed beef is smothered in gravy.

