=== Climate===
Cologne is one of the warmest cities in Germany. It has a [[Temperateness|temperate]]–[[Oceanic climate|oceanic]] climate with relatively mild winters and warm summers. Its average annual temperature is 10 °C (50 °F): 14.5 °C (58 °F) during the day and 5.5 °C (42 °F) at night.
