==Born in Cologne==
Notable people, whose roots can be found in Cologne:
* [[Konrad Adenauer|Adenauer, Konrad]] (5 January 1876 - 19 April 1967), politician, mayor of Cologne (1917–1933, 1945) and first [[Chancellor of Germany (Federal Republic)|West German Federal Chancellor]]
* [[Heinrich Cornelius Agrippa|Agrippa, Heinrich Cornelius]] (1486–1535), alchemist, occultist, and author of [[De occulta philosophia libri tres|Three Books of Occult Philosophy]]
* [[Agrippina the Younger]] (6 November 15 - between 19 March and 23 March 59), Roman Empress (wife of Emperor [[Claudius]]) and mother of Emperor [[Nero]]
* [[Heinrich Birnbaum|Birnbaum, Heinrich]] (1403–1473), a Catholic monk
* [[Robert Blum|Blum, Robert]] (10 November 1807 - 9 November 1848), politician and martyr of the 19th century democratic movement in Germany
* [[Heinrich Böll|Böll, Heinrich]] (21 December 1917 - 16 July 1985), writer and winner of the [[Nobel prize for literature]] in 1972
* [[Max Bruch|Bruch, Max]] (6 January 1838 - 2 October 1920) composer
* [[Álex Calatrava|Calatrava, Álex]] (born 14 June 1973), Spanish professional tennis player
* [[Florian Henckel von Donnersmarck|Donnersmarck, Florian Henckel von]] (born 2 May 1973), [[Academy Award]]-winning director and screenwriter
* [[Max Ernst|Ernst, Max]] (2 April 1891 - 1 April 1976), artist
* [[Angela Gossow|Gossow, Angela]] (5 November 1974) The lead vocalist of the Swedish melodic death metal band Arch Enemy
* [[Britta Heidemann|Heidemann, Britta]] (born 22 December 1982), [[épée]] fencer and [[Olympic medalist]]
* [[:de:Trude Herr|Herr, Trude]] (4 May 1927 - 16 March 1991), actress and singer
* [[:de:Stefanie Höner|Höner, Stefanie]] (born 2 August 1969), actress
* [[Udo Kier|Kier, Udo]] (born 14 October 1944), actor
* [[Jutta Kleinschmidt]] (born August 29, 1962), [[off-road racing|offroad automotive racing]] competitor
* [[Werner Klemperer|Klemperer, Werner]] (22 March 1920 - 6 December 2000), [[Emmy Award]]-winning comedy actor
* [[Erich Klibansky|Klibansky, Erich]] (28 November 1900 - 24 July 1942), Jewish headmaster and teacher
* [[Adolf Kober|Kober, Adolf]] (3 September 1870 - 30 December 1958), Jewish rabbi and medievalist
* [[:de:Hildegard Krekel|Krekel, Hildegard]] (born 2 June 1952), actress
* [[:de:Lotti Krekel|Krekel, Lotti]] (born 23 August 1941), actress and singer
* [[Uwe Krupp|Krupp, Uwe]] (born 24 June 1965), professional (ice) [[Ice hockey|hockey]] player
* [[Heinz Kühn|Kühn, Heinz]] (18 February 1912 - 12 March 1992), [[Minister-President]] of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]] (1966–1978)
* [[Heiner Lauterbach|Lauterbach, Heiner]] (born 10 April 1953), actor
* [[Ottmar Liebert|Liebert, Ottmar]] (born 1 February 1961), musician
* [[Mariele Millowitsch|Millowitsch, Marie-Luise]] (born 23 November 1955), actress
* [[:de:Peter Millowitsch|Millowitsch, Peter]] (born 1 February 1949), actor, [[playwright]] and [[theatre director]]
* [[Willy Millowitsch|Millowitsch, Willy]] (8 January 1909 - 20 September 1999), actor, playwright and theatre director
