* {{Cite book|last=Ferrell|first=Robert H.|authorlink=Robert H. Ferrell|title=The Presidency of Calvin Coolidge|publisher=[[University Press of Kansas]]|year=1998|isbn=978-0-7006-0892-8}}
* {{Cite book|last=Fuess|first=Claude M.|title=Calvin Coolidge: The Man from Vermont'|publisher=Little, Brown|year=1940|isbn=978-1-4067-5673-9}}
* Gilbert, Robert E. &quot;Calvin Coolidge's Tragic Presidency: the Political Effects of Bereavement and Depression.&quot; ''Journal of American Studies'' 2005 39(1): 87-109. Issn: 0021-8758 Fulltext: in Cambridge and Swetswise
* Gilbert, Robert E. ''The Tormented President: Calvin Coolidge, Death, and Clinical Depression.'' Praeger, 2003. 288pp
* {{Cite book|last=Greenberg|first=David|title=Calvin Coolidge|publisher=[[Times Books]]|year=2006|series=The American Presidents Series|isbn=978-0-8050-6957-0}} [http://www.amazon.com/Calvin-Coolidge-David-Greenberg/dp/0805069577/ excerpt and text search]
* Haynes, John Earl, ed. ''Calvin Coolidge and the Coolidge Era: Essays on the History of the 1920s.'' Library of Congress, 1998. 329 pp. essays by scholars
* {{Cite book|last=McCoy|first=Donald R.|title=Calvin Coolidge: The Quiet President|publisher=Macmillan|year=1967|isbn=978-0-945707-23-3}}
