      <text xml:space="preserve">'''Charon''' may refer to:

'''Ancient world'''
*[[Charon (mythology)]], in Greek mythology, the ferryman who ferried the dead to the underworld
*[[Charon of Lampsacus]], ancient Greek logographer (history)
*Charon, a Theban military commander (''fl.'' mid-4th century BC); see [[Androcydes (painter)]]

'''Science, technology and manufacturing'''
*[[Charon (moon)]], a moon of the dwarf planet Pluto
*[[Charon (web browser)]], a web browser for the Inferno operating system
*[[Charon (genus)|''Charon'' (genus)]], a genus of amblypygid
*[[Charon (cars)]], a Dutch automobile manufacturer

'''Popular culture'''
*[[Charon (band)]], a Finnish gothic metal band
*[[Charon (CrossGen)]], a comic book character from CrossGen Entertainment's Sigilverse
*[[Charon (Shun Charon)]], an African-American, aspiring hip hop artist residing in West Virginia. Born in Philadelphia, PA
*[[Charon (DC Comics)]], a DC Comics character based on the mythical figure who has appeared in a number of titles
*[[Charon (Doctor Who)]], a fictional race that was annihilated by the Time Lords before they even existed
*[[Charon (Dungeons &amp; Dragons)]], a lord of the Yugoloths whose primary function is to provide passage across the River Styx for a steep price
*[[Charon (Marvel Comics)]], a villainous wizard
*[[The View from the Mirror|Charon (The Three Worlds)]], a fictional human species from Ian Irvine's arc of novels, ''The Three Worlds Cycle''
*[[Pokémon crime syndicates|Commander Charon]], one of the Galactic Commanders from Pokémon Platinum

'''Video games'''
* Charon, a freighter class capital ship in the MMORPG [[Eve Online]]
* Charon, a deathly mutated man ([[ghoul]]) in [[Fallout 3]] who lives in the [[National Museum of American History]] at a former exhibit on Hell and the afterlife (referred to as &quot;Underworld&quot; in-game).

